<p>This offline teaching system enables users to create NC (numerically controlled) programs and jigs for simultaneous 5-axis laser machining by the minimum amount of workload through the use of 3D CAD data.</p><p>It has been integrated with robust modelling functions of CADmeister. Thus, users can correct models and create laser machining data in one system.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h5><strong>Features</strong></h5><ul><li><u><strong>Intuitive Operability</strong></u></li></ul><p>3D LASER enables users to feel as if they are actually operating a laser machining device.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/5.OTHER/1.3DLASER/LASER_01.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><u><strong>Simulations and Interference&nbsp;Check</strong></u></li></ul><p>3D LASER enables users to simulate actual device movements through the use of machining data and thus to check interferences.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/5.OTHER/1.3DLASER/LASER_02.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><u><strong>Jig Design Functions</strong></u></li></ul><p>3D LASER enables users to design jigs based on the model data through the minimum amount of necessary inputs.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/5.OTHER/1.3DLASER/LASER_03.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/5.OTHER/1.3DLASER/LASER_04.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><u><strong>Re-editing of NC Data</strong></u></li></ul><p>Any existing NC data can be imported and edited.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/5.OTHER/1.3DLASER/LASER_05.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a href="https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1" title="Froala Editor">Froala Editor</a></p>